Natural Language Processing
Natural Language Processing, or NLP for short, is broadly dened as the automatic manipulation
of natural language, like speech and text, by software. The study of natural language processing
has been around for more than 50 years and grew out of the eld of linguistics with the rise of
computers. In this chapter, you will discover what natural language processing is and why it is
so important. After reading this chapter, you will know:
 What natural language is and how it is dierent from other types of data.
 What makes working with natural language so challenging.
 Where the eld of NLP came from and how it is dened by modern practitioners.
Let's get started.
